dcterms:description: The whole-body DXA dataset consists of 99 DXA original samples, provided by Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Fudan University, Shanghai, China. The participants from Shanghai Changfeng Study were scanned over the whole body with lunar iDXA produced by GE company. All these data were converted into images of JPG format with in-plane resolution of 3.0375 mm × 2.4001 mm. Each sample was labelled with 40 contour keypoints by experts.
dcterms:title: Whole-body dual-energy X-ray absorptiometry (DXA) images

dcterms:description: The cardiac MRI dataset consists of 45 LGE CMR sequences, collected from Shanghai Renji hospital. Each sequence contains 10 to 18 slices with in-plane resolution of 1 mm × 1 mm, covering the main body of the ventricles. The segmentation ground truth for left ventricle (LV), right ventricle (RV) and myocardium (Myo) were provided by experts.
dcterms:title: Cardiac MRI images

dcterms:description: The whole-head CT dataset has 54 whole-head CT images from different participants, provided by Huashan Hospital affiliated to Fudan University, Shanghai, China. Each volume was manually labeled by experts with 25 anatomical skull landmarks.
dcterms:title: Whole-head CT images

dcterms:description: The half-head CT dataset consists of 41 upper-half head CT volumes from the Northern Han Chinese cohort, which was provided by Shanghai Institute of Nutrition and Health, Chinese Academy of Sciences. The number of landmarks in these volumes varies from 14 to 19 according to the position of intersecting surface.
dcterms:title: Half-head CT images
